[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMongoose JSON parser. The overflow occurs in the function `mg_json_get` when [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwriting one byte past the end of a local array named `nesting`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  While running the libFuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reported a one-byte write beyond the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds of a stack-allocated buffer inside the function `mg_json_get` [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`src/mongoose/src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The buffer in question, `nesting`, is allocated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bytes but is accessed at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, causing a stack-buffer-overflow.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is a stack-based buffer overflow vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASan report: [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“stack-buffer-overflow”[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations and findings  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The crash happens in `mg_json_get`, which is part of the JSON parsing [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The local array `nesting` is defined with a size of [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bytes, but the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer-generated input triggers an index of [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, writing outside its bounds.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The overflow is detected when `mg_json_get` attempts to write one byte past [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m31[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The fuzzer entry point is `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads arbitrary input and passes it to the JSON parser.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **Function `mg_json_get` in `src/mongoose/src/json.c`**  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Definition and size of the `nesting` array [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m127[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Logic that increments or indexes into `nesting` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mleading up to line [0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **Fuzzer harness in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c`**  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - The way input is fed to `mg_json_get` or related parsing functions.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **JSON parser control flow**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Any loops or recursive calls in the parser that manage depth or nesting [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounters.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThese components should be reviewed together to understand how input-driven [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindexing into `nesting` can exceed its allocated size and cause this overflow.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocal array `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault size [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpermits nesting up to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. When parsing deeply [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested JSON arrays [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or objects [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m beyond [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m levels, the code writes to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` with `depth` up to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m, overrunning the [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte buffer.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insight[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must synchronize the buffer size used for tracking nesting with the maximum[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting depth allowed by the parser’s logic.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rather than shrinking the logic’s allowed depth [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhich could silently truncate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid use cases[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we should enlarge the buffer to cover the full permitted range.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Steps[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/mongoose/src/json.c`, locate the declaration:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Replace it with a declaration sized against `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplus one [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto cover indexing at `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. No other logic changes are required: the existing overflow check[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      still prevents writes at `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, and by allocating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` bytes, writes at indices `[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` are now[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin bounds.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Functionality[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Parsing logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth checks, path matching, return-value computations[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muntouched.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness and all existing tests continue to operate over the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI, with the only change being the capacity of the stack buffer.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification & Side Effects[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Safety: Completely prevents the one‐byte overflow observed by ASan.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Minimal impact: The buffer grows from [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m61[0m[39m bytes—negligible on typical [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstacks.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Backward settings: If users override `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, the buffer [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mauto‐scales—and no inconsistency arises.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change to fuzzing or harness code; existing coverage remains valid.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run AddressSanitizer‐enabled fuzzing; the stack-buffer-overflow in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` must no longer occur.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Execute regression test suite to confirm no unintended behavior changes.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Optionally add a new unit‐test for deep‐nesting close to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto verify correct operation up to the declared limit.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where the local array `nesting` is overrun by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone byte. A patch attempt increased the size of `nesting` from `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`. After rebuilding and re-running the fuzzer for [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mruns, the same stack-buffer-overflow at the same location persists, indicating the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch did not eliminate the overflow.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - During fuzzing [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reports:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address corresponding to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the stack frame, beyond the bounds of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `nesting` array.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • The call stack shows the error originates at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `src/json.c` in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`, invoked by the fuzz test harness in `test/fuzz.c`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Shadow bytes indicate the redzone begins immediately after the valid `nesting`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion, confirming a one-byte overflow.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The reported overflow offset [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exceeds the declared bounds of `nesting`.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `nesting` array is used to track nesting levels while parsing JSON.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure reproducibly occurs on malformed or deeply nested input provided [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the fuzzer.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original declaration [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m of `json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patched declaration:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other changes were made in `mg_json_get`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, rebuilding, and running the same fuzz target for [0m[1;36m100[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterations, AddressSanitizer reports an identical stack-buffer-overflow at the same[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode location.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow still occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, suggesting the new array size is still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsufficient for the nesting depth reached by the test case.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definitions and relationships of the macros `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to ensure they reflect the maximum possible depth encountered[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `mg_json_get` around incrementing and using the `depth` index [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen writing to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any loops or recursive calls in `mg_json_get` that manipulate `depth` without [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Align `nesting` buffer with the maximum allowed nesting depth:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace all uses of the separate `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` macro in `mg_json_get` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`, so that the buffer size matches exactly the highest[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth we allow at runtime.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In practice, change:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     to[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m MAX_DEPTH = MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures the stack buffer can hold indices [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m through [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Tighten the depth‐overflow checks to prevent any out‐of‐bounds writes:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before every `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` assignment [0m[1;39m([0m[39mboth in the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbranches[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     so that once `depth` reaches `MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e. `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstop parsing and return `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` without writing into `nesting`.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Remove the old `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` dependency in this function:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After adopting `MAX_DEPTH`, references to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` inside `json.c` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan be deleted, avoiding confusion and ensuring only one macro governs the buffer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize and bounds.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Validate macro definitions in `json.h`:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` is always defined [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefaulting to [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minclusion of `json.c`.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If project‐level overrides exist, ensure they redefine `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly and not `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preserve existing behavior:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The change does not alter the JSON parsing semantics or the return codes.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When the input nesting exceeds the configured limit, `mg_json_get` still [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`, consistent with prior behavior.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Testing and verification:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuild the code and rerun the fuzzer; the stack-buffer-overflow should no [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlonger trigger because writes into `nesting` are now safely bounded.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing unit tests and the fuzz harness remain unchanged.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The root cause was a mismatch between the buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginally [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe maximum nesting the code allowed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mup to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m levels before signaling [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, leading to writes beyond the buffer.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The prior patch changed only the buffer size but still relied on two macros [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` vs. `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which led to inconsistent builds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the buffer did not actually grow.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By unifying the buffer dimension [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MAX_DEPTH = MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtightening the bounds check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`depth >= MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we ensure no off‐by‐one or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro‐mismatch errors cause overflows.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This minimal invasive change preserves existing logic, avoids altering harness [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode or tests, and ensures correct buffer bounds at compile time and at runtime.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msrc/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing certain inputs. The overflow occurs in the local array[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m. A patch was proposed that [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m redefines the buffer size to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` via a new `MAX_DEPTH` constant and [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m tightens the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth‐check conditions from `>` to `>= MAX_DEPTH`. After applying the patch, the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame AddressSanitizer error recurs at the same location and offset, indicating that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer overflow remains unaddressed.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash report shows an AddressSanitizer “stack-buffer-overflow” at [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m in json.c.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow writes one byte past the end of the local array `unsigned char [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan indicates that the overflow happens at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m into the `nesting` array [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhose valid range is [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m61[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace shows the overflow trial during JSON parsing triggered by [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The buffer `nesting` is allocated on the stack and sized by `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code increments `depth` and indexes `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` when encountering `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` without sufficient bounds checks.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow occurs before any heap allocations or other modules; the root is in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe JSON parsing routine.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In lines [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m132[0m[39m of json.c, `nesting` was changed from  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  to  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m MAX_DEPTH = MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING + [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:167[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m173[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Unify buffer size and depth‐limit constant by using MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING for both[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation and checks.  This resolves the root‐cause mismatch [0m[1;39m([0m[33mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m30[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvs. [0m[33mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and eliminates the off‐by‐one condition.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In src/json.c, revert the last attempt’s local MAX_DEPTH enum and instead:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the nesting‐buffer declaration from:[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to:[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Change the two pre‐push checks  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      to use `>=` and the same constant:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – apply this in both the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` branches immediately before [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Do not modify json.h’s defines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mother than ensuring MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING remains [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m by default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  By allocating the buffer to MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING entries and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarding writes with `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, the code now safely supports [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mup to [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m levels of nesting without overflow.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preserve the existing JSON‐path logic, return codes, and fuzzer harness.  No [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother parts of mg_json_get, test, or harness code are altered.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Validate the patch by rebuilding and re‐running the fuzzer:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Confirm that no stack‐buffer‐overflow is reported in mg_json_get.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Confirm MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP is returned on inputs exceeding the [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m‐level limit.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By using the same macro for both the stack array size and the depth‐check limit, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` are constrained within correct bounds.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Switching the check from `>` to `>=` closes the off‐by‐one gap that previously [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowed one extra write past the buffer end.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This minimal change preserves the original parsing logic and existing tests, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes not alter fuzzing or harness code.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar one‐macro solutions appear in other modules [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., URI parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer sizes and limit checks are driven by the same constant.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer-driven test of the `mg_json_get` function in `src/json.c` triggers an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer crash reporting a stack-buffer-overflow in the local array [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`. The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of the array, suggesting that the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared size does not accommodate all writes.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was applied to change the declaration of `nesting` from size [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and to tighten the boundary checks by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplacing `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` with `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` for [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m nesting cases. After rebuilding and rerunning the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer, the same stack-buffer-overflow is reported at the same location, indicating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the patch did not eliminate the overflow.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invokes `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which calls `mg_json_get` in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/json.c`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a one‐byte write beyond the end of the local stack [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marray `nesting` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack frame shows `nesting` spans offsets [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m61[0m[39m, yet a write occurs at [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other errors or alternative crash sites are reported—this is a reproducible[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow in `mg_json_get`.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations from the Crash Log  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash is classified as `stack-buffer-overflow` with “SCARINESS: [0m[1;36m46[0m[39m.”  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The backtrace identifies:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Frame [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m: `mg_json_get`, `json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Frame [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, `test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81:3[0m[39m`  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Frames [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m5[0m[39m: libFuzzer internals and `main`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Shadow byte legend indicates a write into the “Stack mid redzone” for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local variable `nesting` is the only object in the frame, confirming the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow target.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File modified: `src/json.c`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Original code [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m127[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m S_VALUE, S_KEY, S_COLON, S_COMMA_OR_EOO [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m expecting = S_VALUE;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, j = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, depth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Patched code:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[33m...[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[33m...[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The change replaces `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` with `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtightens the checks from `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` before incrementing `depth`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Test Results  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The same AddressSanitizer error is reported in `mg_json_get` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow still occurs at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the `nesting` array.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No new errors or differences in backtrace location are observed.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definitions of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`—ensure they [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatch intended limits.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All uses of `depth` when indexing `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, including pre- and [0m             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The loop and state machine in `mg_json_get` that advance `depth` on `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` and decrement on `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Boundary conditions in path parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvariables `ed`, `pos`, `ci`, `ei`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay drive `depth` past the array bounds.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any related constants or invariants in `src/json.h` or other JSON utility [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzz harness in `test/fuzz.c` to understand how input shapes calls into [0m   [2m                [0m
