[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:129[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m137[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:  enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m S_VALUE, S_KEY, S_COLON, S_COMMA_OR_EOO [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m expecting = S_VALUE;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:  unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:  int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current offset in `s`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:  int j = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Offset in `s` we're looking for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn value[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:  int depth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current depth [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting level[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:  int ed = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Expected depth[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:  int pos = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current position in `path`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:  int ci = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current and expected index in array[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:163[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m173[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m163[0m[39m:      case S_VALUE:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m164[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35mp[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"V %s [0m[32m[[0m[32m%.*s[0m[32m][0m[32m %d %d %d %d\n"[0m[39m, path, pos, path, depth, ed, ci, ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m165[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m j = i;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause and Core Insight  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local array `nesting` in `mg_json_get` is sized with `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, while all the boundary checks use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This mismatch permits up to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m nested `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` before error, but the buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly holds [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes, causing writes past the end. Even after the last patch, this [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfundamental mismatch remains [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASan still reports a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m-byte buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so the overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High-Level Strategy  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Consolidate to a single depth constant to eliminate the mismatch.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure both the stack buffer size and the “too deep” checks use that same [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Use the stricter “>=” comparison to block any write at index == capacity.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Concrete Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `src/json.h`, collapse `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` into [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone consistent macro, e.g.:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Alias/deprecate MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING—keep it in sync *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This ensures both names refer to the same value.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove the hard-coded `[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m` default for `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `src/json.c`, use only `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its alias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for both buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizing and boundary checks:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change the buffer declaration back to:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace every `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` in the “too deep?” checks with [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Keep the “>=” operator so when `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, we return [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` before any write.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Verify the logic around `depth`:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - On encountering `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, do:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - No other code paths write to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, so this single guard prevents [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOOB.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Behavior  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rejecting any JSON deeper than [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m levels is consistent with the original [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness, path parsing logic, and all other state transitions remain[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests that exercise shallower JSON survive unmodified.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Some users who expected [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m levels may now hit “too deep” at [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m. If [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m levels [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare required, simply bump `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand thus `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone place.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No change to harness or test code—fuzzing will still drive the same code [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths, now with proper safety checks.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Similar Patterns  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other parts of the codebase use a single `MG_FOO_MAX` macro for both buffer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizing and limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in URI parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Follow that pattern here.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   By collapsing to one macro—`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`—for both the array size and the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth limit, and using a strict `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= limit[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check, we remove the mismatch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat permitted the stack buffer overflow. This approach is minimal, keeps the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpublic API unchanged, and localizes the change to two files [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.h` and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/28/25 01:14:47][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=419762;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=1879;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m5[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.VULNERABLE[1m)[0m                                   [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report revealed a stack-buffer-overflow in the function [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile `json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during fuzz testing.  The overflow occurs when [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwriting one byte past the end of a local array named `nesting`.  A patch was [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted that:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed the default `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` macro to use `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified two conditional checks on `depth` for object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entry[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same stack-buffer-overflow still occurs at [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`, indicating the patch did not prevent the out-of-bounds write.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ERROR: AddressSanitizer: stack-buffer-overflow on address [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m thread T0[0m      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Address [0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m is located in stack of thread T0 at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in frame[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m  mg_json_get [0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m127[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[32m'nesting'[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m131[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <== Memory access at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m overflows this [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local array `nesting` has size up to offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes if entries are [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes each, or [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m bytes if entries are single bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but an index write reaches [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly that boundary, overflowing by one.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations and findings  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure site is inside `mg_json_get`, on line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`, where code [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites into `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` or a similarly indexed structure.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The default macro in `src/json.h` reads:[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash implies that under certain inputs the code allows `depth` to equal [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor exceed the array’s capacity before returning `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.h`, the patch replaced:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, two blocks were altered:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     for both the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` branches.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intention was to unify nesting limits and tighten the depth check.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result after patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzing logs post-patch show the same sanitizer error:[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:166[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m173[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m166[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:          expecting = S_KEY;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause and Core Insight  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack buffer `nesting` is declared as `unsigned char [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The two critical write sites [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m live under the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` parsing branches in `[0m[1;35mmg_json_get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both branches previously guarded with the *wrong* macro [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, default [0m[1;36m60[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and with a “>” test, allowing writes up to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindex [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m into a [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte buffer.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The last patch attempted to switch to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and “>=” tests but [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdid not eliminate all mismatch points between the guard and array size, so writes [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill occur at `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mindex [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, overflowing the [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m29[0m[39m array.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Unify on a single depth limit macro [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for both array size[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand bounds checking; drop the unused `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. In `src/json.h`:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove or comment out the `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` block entirely.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Retain only:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         #endif[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Optionally add a static assertion or comment reminding maintainers that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis value controls both array size and guard thresholds.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. In `src/json.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside `mg_json_get`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Delete all references to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. For both the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` branches, replace the old guard and write [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequence with the precise check:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         depth++;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         This guarantees that `depth` is strictly less than the buffer capacity [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore any write.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure no other code path in the function writes to `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` without [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same `>= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` check.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Add a simple compile‐time static assertion [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere supported[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or a comment:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Ensure the nesting buffer is large enough for the declared maximum depth[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;35m_Static_assert[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[32m"MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH must be [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mpositive"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing parsing branches, depth‐tracking logic, path‐matching behavior, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand return values remain unchanged except that overly deep inputs now return [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` one step earlier, preventing out‐of‐bounds writes.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Removing `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` does not affect other code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mit was only used in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthese guards[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer harnesses, tests, and public APIs on `mg_json_get` are preserved; the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly change is earlier depth‐limit enforcement.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Is Optimal  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Eliminates the macro mismatch that has caused repeated mis‐patches.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consolidates all “maximum nesting” concerns under one macro, reducing future [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintenance errors.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses a clear `>=` check instead of `>` plus a separate macro alias; this [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern is idiomatic and less error‐prone.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Avoids expanding the buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno new memory[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so stack usage remains bounded as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginally intended.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No modifications to fuzzing harness, test files, or utility code—only the core[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJSON parser.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Very deeply nested JSON [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdeeper than [0m[1;36m29[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will be rejected sooner [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturning [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Clients relying on deeper nesting must increase [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` before compilation.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The static assertion ensures that maintainers cannot inadvertently set a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon‐positive depth.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because only out‐of‐bounds writes are changed, there is minimal risk of [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltering correct behavior on well‐formed, shallow JSON.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A quick unit test [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconstructing a [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m‐level‐deep JSON string[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can verify that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe function bails without overflow.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No External or Harness Changes  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This strategy strictly modifies `src/json.h` and `src/json.c`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzz harness in `test/fuzz.c`, any third‐party dependencies, and test [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles remain untouched.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy unifying on `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and enforcing `depth < MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` before[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach write, the stack‐buffer overflow is fully prevented while preserving all [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting JSON parsing logic.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
